parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while making a turn
the vehicle stalls when accelerating
the fuel system "gasps" and does not respond to acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck deceleration valve can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle does not respond to acceleration
the deceleration valve is stuck closed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to repair a recalled vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle was not repaired under recall
the vehicle stalled despite being recalled for stalling issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected acceleration
vehicle surges forward without driver input
vehicle stalls after acceleration
difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the electronic throttle control can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected acceleration
vehicle surges forward without driver input
difficulty stopping the vehicle
engine RPM increases without driver input.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling due to Faulty MAP Sensor and Ignition Control Module
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the MAP sensor and Ignition Control Module can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off while driving
the vehicle loses power
the engine hesitates or stumbles
the check engine light illuminates
the vehicle experiences difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Voltage Meter Printed Circuit Board Overheating
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the voltage meter printed circuit board can cause components to fail, leading to battery and alternator damage, which can result in electrical system failures, stalling, and potentially even a vehicle fire.
symptoms: The voltage meter is not functioning correctly
the voltage meter is displaying incorrect readings
the dashboard lights are flickering or dimming
the battery is draining excessively
the alternator is not charging the battery properly.
